  "text": "At this point it is important to remark that if we attempt to construct the free energy from the expression, Ω(A, T ) = −P A with the pressure given by Eq. (5) we see that the thermodynamic equations (11) give the entropy as in Eq. (9) and an incorrect expression for the pressure. The reason why the last construction fails is because the energy U (A, T ) is not a homogeneous function of order one in its extensive variables and, as a consequence of this, the Euler relation U = T S − P A does not hold, which is a necessary requirement for the free energy to be given by Ω = −P A [CITATION_1] . This is a particular feature of the LL thermodynamic relations. Therefore, we need to construct the free energy Ω(A, T ) from the differential relation [CITATION_2] . Using the input, that is the pressure (5), and imposing that the entropy at the origin vanishes we get the following free energy",
